pamir-ai-eink-dkms (1.0.0-2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Split driver into modular components (core, hw, display, fb, sysfs)
  * Added three update modes: full refresh, partial update, base map
  * Implemented mmap support with vmalloc_user for framebuffer access
  * Added IOCTL interface for userspace control
  * Added sysfs attributes for runtime configuration
  * Fixed kernel coding style compliance issues
  * Added SSD1680 deep sleep mode
  * Improved SPI error handling with retry logic
  * Added C and Python example programs

 -- Pamir AI <support@pamir.ai>  Thu, 28 Aug 2025 01:09:58 +0530

pamir-ai-eink-dkms (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release of Pamir AI E-Ink framebuffer driver

